  • Deprecated Classes 
    Class and Description
    com.launchdarkly.client.SegmentRule
    This class was made public in error and will be removed in a future release. It is used internally by the SDK.
    com.launchdarkly.client.TestFeatureStore
    Will be replaced by a file-based test fixture.
    com.launchdarkly.client.UpdateProcessor.NullUpdateProcessor
    Use Components.nullUpdateProcessor() instead of referring to this implementation class directly.
  • Deprecated Enums 
    Enum and Description
    com.launchdarkly.client.LDCountryCode
  • Deprecated Fields 
    Field and Description
    com.launchdarkly.client.RedisFeatureStoreBuilder.DEFAULT_CACHE_TIME_SECONDS
    Use FeatureStoreCacheConfig.DEFAULT.
  • Deprecated Methods 
    Method and Description
    com.launchdarkly.client.LDClientInterface.allFlags(LDUser)
    Use LDClientInterface.allFlagsState(com.launchdarkly.client.LDUser, com.launchdarkly.client.FlagsStateOption...) instead. Current versions of the client-side SDK will not generate analytics events correctly if you pass the result of allFlags().
    com.launchdarkly.client.value.LDValue.asJsonElement()
    The Gson types may be removed from the public API at some point; it is preferable to use getters like LDValue.booleanValue() and LDValue.getType().
    com.launchdarkly.client.value.LDValue.asUnsafeJsonElement()
    This method will be removed in a future version. Application code should always use LDValue.asJsonElement().
    com.launchdarkly.client.RedisFeatureStoreBuilder.asyncRefresh(boolean)
    Use RedisFeatureStoreBuilder.caching(FeatureStoreCacheConfig) and FeatureStoreCacheConfig.staleValuesPolicy(com.launchdarkly.client.FeatureStoreCacheConfig.StaleValuesPolicy).
    com.launchdarkly.client.RedisFeatureStoreBuilder.cacheTime(long, TimeUnit)
    use RedisFeatureStoreBuilder.caching(FeatureStoreCacheConfig) and FeatureStoreCacheConfig.ttl(long, TimeUnit).
    com.launchdarkly.client.LDUser.Builder.country(LDCountryCode)
    As of version 4.10.0. In the next major release the SDK will no longer include the LDCountryCode class. Applications should use LDUser.Builder.country(String) instead.
    com.launchdarkly.client.LDUser.Builder.custom(String, JsonElement)
    Use LDUser.Builder.custom(String, LDValue).
    com.launchdarkly.client.LDConfig.Builder.featureStore(FeatureStore)
    Please use LDConfig.Builder.featureStoreFactory(FeatureStoreFactory).
    com.launchdarkly.client.value.LDValue.fromJsonElement(JsonElement)
    The Gson types may be removed from the public API at some point; it is preferable to use factory methods like LDValue.of(boolean).
    com.launchdarkly.client.LDClientInterface.jsonVariation(String, LDUser, JsonElement)
    Use LDClientInterface.jsonValueVariation(String, LDUser, LDValue). Gson types may be removed from the public API in the future.
    com.launchdarkly.client.LDClientInterface.jsonVariationDetail(String, LDUser, JsonElement)
    Use LDClientInterface.jsonValueVariationDetail(String, LDUser, LDValue). Gson types may be removed from the public API in the future.
    com.launchdarkly.client.LDUser.Builder.privateCountry(LDCountryCode)
    As of version 4.10.0. In the next major release the SDK will no longer include the LDCountryCode class. Applications should use LDUser.Builder.privateCountry(String) instead.
    com.launchdarkly.client.LDUser.Builder.privateCustom(String, JsonElement)
    Use LDUser.Builder.privateCustom(String, LDValue).
    com.launchdarkly.client.RedisFeatureStoreBuilder.refreshStaleValues(boolean)
    Use RedisFeatureStoreBuilder.caching(FeatureStoreCacheConfig) and FeatureStoreCacheConfig.staleValuesPolicy(com.launchdarkly.client.FeatureStoreCacheConfig.StaleValuesPolicy).
    com.launchdarkly.client.LDConfig.Builder.samplingInterval(int)
    This feature will be removed in a future version of the SDK.
    com.launchdarkly.client.LDClientInterface.track(String, LDUser, JsonElement)
    Use LDClientInterface.trackData(String, LDUser, LDValue).
    com.launchdarkly.client.LDClientInterface.track(String, LDUser, JsonElement, double)
    Use LDClientInterface.trackMetric(String, LDUser, LDValue, double).
    com.launchdarkly.client.value.LDValue.unsafeFromJsonElement(JsonElement)
    This method will be removed in a future version. Application code should use LDValue.fromJsonElement(JsonElement) or, preferably, factory methods like LDValue.of(boolean).
